To find the $\goldE{\text{total}}$ height of the Dragon's house, we start with the height of the $\blueE{\text{Giant's house}}$, and add how many $\maroonD{\text{meters shorter}}$ it is.

![](web+graphie://cdn.kastatic.org/ka-perseus-graphie/74c29a58dbaab6798cdc3e5aebcc0a9518aca123)

$\begin{align}
\blueE{\text{Giant's house}} + \maroonD{35}  &= \goldE{\text{Dragon's house}} \\\\
\blueE{23} + \maroonD{35} &= \goldE{\Box}
\end{align}$
